				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Delta {{E}}_{{{LE}},{{CT}}}$$\end{document} of about 0.13 eV. Given the overall driving force (HOMO offset) of 0.21 eV, this value suggests a positive driving force for charge separation. However, there is substantial uncertainty in this value due to the limitations of the calculation, describing the interaction between a single donor monomer and a single acceptor molecule.

